  "title": "Spring's First Blossom",
  "secondName": "Spring's First Blossom",
  "description": "Rizette's hometown welcomed the New Year warmly, but with little fanfare. She remembers the fragrant bread and soup her mother would make, how she and Theo would run around the house, banishing evil spirits with brooms and feather dusters. After dinner, with bellies full and fire crackling, her father would lean back in his chair and read from their book of fairy tales. Theo always fell asleep before he finished.\n\nCompared to the lanterns and fireworks of the capital, the New Year of her home is nothing. But she misses it all the same.",
